Futurama is an American animated science fiction sitcom created by Matt Groening for the Fox Broadcasting Company. The series follows the adventures of a late 20th-century pizza delivery boy, Philip J. Fry, after being unwittingly cryogenically frozen for a thousand years. In the united states, the series aired from March 28, 1999 to August 10, 2003 on Fox before ceasing production.
